  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "Occurs when normally elastic pericardium becomes thickened and fibrotic (i.e., loss of elasticiticty)\n[1]\nCan be infectious, post-cardiac surgery, inflammatory, idiopathic or related to radiation exposure\n[2]\nImpairs diastolic filling of heart\nMust distinguish from\nrestrictive cardiomyopathy\nTypically chronic complication of\npericarditis",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "restrictive cardiomyopathy",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Restrictive_cardiomyopathy"
        },
        {
          "text": "pericarditis",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Pericarditis"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Pleuritic chest pain\nMalaise\nSymptoms similar to\ncongestive heart failure\n, especially right sided\nDyspnea\nLower extremity edema\nJugular venous distention\nCharacteristic symptoms of\npericarditis\nless frequent in recurrent presentations",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "congestive heart failure",
